1
00:00:00,534 --> 00:00:01,806
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,806 --> 00:00:03,070
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,371 --> 00:00:05,806
(Episode 40)

4
00:00:06,871 --> 00:00:09,965
Seung Ri, I'm sorry, but...

5
00:00:12,598 --> 00:00:13,981
there's someone I like.

6
00:00:16,730 --> 00:00:17,879
Gyeol.

7
00:00:19,871 --> 00:00:22,322
This feeling is unfamiliar to me too.

8
00:00:22,804 --> 00:00:26,260
So it took me a long time to realize it.

9
00:00:27,469 --> 00:00:30,163
But now, I know for sure...

10
00:00:31,404 --> 00:00:33,767
that I really like her.

11
00:00:37,871 --> 00:00:40,207
Who is that person?

12
00:00:41,217 --> 00:00:42,876
Whoever it is, one thing's certain.

13
00:00:43,671 --> 00:00:44,771
In my heart,

14
00:00:45,371 --> 00:00:48,071
there's no place for you
other than as a friend.

15
00:00:49,338 --> 00:00:50,399
So...

16
00:00:51,384 --> 00:00:54,622
please let go of your feelings for me,
Seung Ri.

17
00:00:58,504 --> 00:00:59,671
It's Ms. Cho Eun Ae, isn't it?

18
00:01:01,624 --> 00:01:03,324
Seo Seung Ri.

19
00:01:05,817 --> 00:01:07,717
I know you had a birthday party with her.

20
00:01:08,764 --> 00:01:10,640
All this time,
even though I wanted to congratulate you,

21
00:01:10,640 --> 00:01:13,040
I held back so I wouldn't hurt you.

22
00:01:14,844 --> 00:01:16,944
Let's not talk about someone
who isn't here.

23
00:01:16,944 --> 00:01:20,881
It's because I know
who made you open your heart.

24
00:01:26,704 --> 00:01:28,455
How are you getting home?

25
00:01:28,455 --> 00:01:30,271
Shall we meet where I dropped you off
this morning?

26
00:01:30,271 --> 00:01:32,200
No, I have plans tonight.

27
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:33,226
Go home on your own.

28
00:01:34,371 --> 00:01:35,862
What kind of plans?

29
00:01:37,531 --> 00:01:38,799
Why do I even care?

30
00:01:40,304 --> 00:01:41,902
At times like this, running is the answer.

31
00:01:43,930 --> 00:01:45,171
Go wash up quickly...

32
00:01:45,171 --> 00:01:47,183
if you don't want to run into
the Team Manager in the bathroom.

33
00:01:47,183 --> 00:01:48,650
I'll wash up after I get back from my run.

34
00:01:54,104 --> 00:01:57,736
Stolen lotion really does smell better.

35
00:02:01,871 --> 00:02:02,871
You're studying hard.

36
00:02:03,971 --> 00:02:05,264
Of course I am.

37
00:02:05,264 --> 00:02:08,264
I have to compete
with those sharp young kids.

38
00:02:09,232 --> 00:02:12,432
By the way, why hasn't your team manager
come home yet?

39
00:02:13,071 --> 00:02:14,071
I don't know.

40
00:02:16,704 --> 00:02:18,623
Mom,
you still have the deposit and rent...

41
00:02:18,623 --> 00:02:20,723
you got from Team Manager, right?

42
00:02:21,004 --> 00:02:22,071
Let's return them.

43
00:02:22,071 --> 00:02:23,144
What?

44
00:02:23,144 --> 00:02:25,879
Tell him to move out.

45
00:02:26,371 --> 00:02:28,348
Why? Did something happen between you two?

46
00:02:28,671 --> 00:02:29,971
It's not like that.

47
00:02:29,971 --> 00:02:31,529
Then no.

48
00:02:31,671 --> 00:02:35,322
And do you think terminating a contract
is that easy?

49
00:02:36,304 --> 00:02:38,604
I'm just relieved it's not some stranger,

50
00:02:38,604 --> 00:02:41,228
but someone you and your dad both know.

51
00:02:41,228 --> 00:02:42,518
Think about it.

52
00:02:42,518 --> 00:02:44,371
My boss lives right across from me.

53
00:02:44,371 --> 00:02:46,771
I can't just wear whatever
and walk around,

54
00:02:46,771 --> 00:02:48,635
or sit in the bathroom for too long.

55
00:02:48,971 --> 00:02:50,071
Just hang in there for a bit.

56
00:02:50,071 --> 00:02:52,304
It's not even for a year.
It's only a four-month lease.

57
00:02:52,671 --> 00:02:56,176
And besides, there was no one else
who wanted to rent it.

58
00:02:56,176 --> 00:02:58,871
A tenant will show up if we wait.

59
00:02:59,079 --> 00:03:00,263
So come on...

60
00:03:00,263 --> 00:03:02,830
I need to study, you know.

61
00:03:03,671 --> 00:03:05,819
Mom.

62
00:03:06,921 --> 00:03:10,223
What? You want me
to make side dishes for your studio?

63
00:03:10,223 --> 00:03:13,894
Yeah, like kimchi and other side dishes...

64
00:03:15,404 --> 00:03:17,171
Things that are good as late-night snacks.

65
00:03:17,171 --> 00:03:18,298
Pack me some of those.

66
00:03:19,664 --> 00:03:20,931
Are you moving out altogether?

67
00:03:22,470 --> 00:03:24,671
There's no bedroom.
How would I even live there?

68
00:03:24,671 --> 00:03:27,791
You can just eat breakfast and dinner
at home...

69
00:03:28,282 --> 00:03:30,371
and have lunch out. What's the problem?

70
00:03:30,371 --> 00:03:34,479
Mom, I'm an artist, okay?

71
00:03:34,811 --> 00:03:38,044
I can't live on a fixed schedule...

72
00:03:38,044 --> 00:03:40,104
like a civil servant
going to and from work.

73
00:03:40,604 --> 00:03:43,571
If I'm working,
I might have to pull all-nighters.

74
00:03:43,571 --> 00:03:45,371
It's a studio, after all.

75
00:03:45,371 --> 00:03:47,271
Treat it like commuting.

76
00:03:47,271 --> 00:03:48,971
It's better for your health.

77
00:03:48,971 --> 00:03:51,465
By the way,
how's the writer you're working with?

78
00:03:51,904 --> 00:03:53,600
What do you mean? In what way?

79
00:03:53,804 --> 00:03:55,771
From what I heard
when you were on the phone last time,

80
00:03:55,771 --> 00:03:58,971
she sounded pretty arrogant and cold
just because she's doing well.

81
00:04:01,204 --> 00:04:02,271
No, it's not like that.

82
00:04:02,771 --> 00:04:04,344
Once we actually started working,

83
00:04:04,817 --> 00:04:07,777
perhaps because she's so professional,
none of those issues came up at all.

84
00:04:08,371 --> 00:04:10,083
She really respects me.

85
00:04:11,071 --> 00:04:12,552
Yeah, respect.

86
00:04:14,837 --> 00:04:17,557
Doesn't look like it from your face.

87
00:04:17,698 --> 00:04:18,871
I'm home.

88
00:04:18,871 --> 00:04:20,694
Welcome. You're late.

89
00:04:21,411 --> 00:04:23,004
Yes, I had something to take care of.

90
00:04:23,004 --> 00:04:24,130
Seo Seung Ri!

91
00:04:24,671 --> 00:04:27,684
I started working at the studio today.
It's day one.

92
00:04:28,090 --> 00:04:29,769
I'm tired, so I'll head in first.

93
00:04:31,571 --> 00:04:32,704
What's with her now?

94
00:04:32,704 --> 00:04:35,175
Leave her. She said she's tired.

95
00:04:46,704 --> 00:04:48,555
What exactly is Ms. Cho Eun Ae to you?

96
00:04:49,404 --> 00:04:51,391
What makes her so special?

97
00:04:51,931 --> 00:04:55,228
Seo Seung Ri,
you're also someone special to me.

98
00:04:55,703 --> 00:04:58,736
I hope you meet someone
who recognizes how special you are...

99
00:04:59,271 --> 00:05:01,671
and truly cherishes you.

100
00:05:03,304 --> 00:05:04,437
Gyeol, you really...

101
00:05:06,671 --> 00:05:08,275
Do you know how cruel you are to me?

102
00:05:10,458 --> 00:05:11,512
I'm sorry.

103
00:05:12,971 --> 00:05:14,114
So...

104
00:05:15,471 --> 00:05:17,271
please don't make me feel guilty anymore.

105
00:05:19,071 --> 00:05:23,085
I genuinely want you to be happy.

106
00:06:02,571 --> 00:06:03,797
You work out too?

107
00:06:04,671 --> 00:06:08,068
Yes,
a night workout is how I wrap up my day.

108
00:06:08,371 --> 00:06:09,869
It's part of my routine.

109
00:06:10,571 --> 00:06:11,571
I see your routine.

110
00:06:11,871 --> 00:06:14,371
Isn't your routine
getting drunk and stumbling home?

111
00:06:14,371 --> 00:06:15,371
Seriously.

112
00:06:16,371 --> 00:06:18,971
Yesterday really was the first time
in ages.

113
00:06:18,971 --> 00:06:22,449
Really? From what I remember,
you recently...

114
00:06:22,449 --> 00:06:24,671
You've got a great memory for no reason.

115
00:06:27,571 --> 00:06:30,171
So who did you meet?

116
00:06:30,831 --> 00:06:32,516
Curious? If you're curious...

117
00:06:32,516 --> 00:06:34,149
"Hand over 50 cents." Am I right?

118
00:06:35,704 --> 00:06:38,431
What is this, some archaic joke?

119
00:06:39,171 --> 00:06:40,204
Don't do that.

120
00:06:41,504 --> 00:06:42,602
Is that so?

121
00:06:50,904 --> 00:06:53,413
I think I get it.

122
00:06:54,371 --> 00:06:55,471
Get what?

123
00:06:55,471 --> 00:06:58,885
That you feel at ease
when you come into this neighborhood.

124
00:07:00,271 --> 00:07:03,189
You've only lived here a day.
Someone might think you're a local.

125
00:07:05,671 --> 00:07:07,971
Anyway, how long are you planning
to stay at my place?

126
00:07:08,471 --> 00:07:09,896
You'll find another place
and move out, right?

127
00:07:10,071 --> 00:07:11,131
Why should I?

128
00:07:11,367 --> 00:07:13,667
I'm a tenant who signed a proper contract.

129
00:07:13,871 --> 00:07:15,404
Telling me to move out like this...

130
00:07:15,404 --> 00:07:17,437
is a violation
of the Housing Lease Protection Act.

131
00:07:17,871 --> 00:07:18,871
There you go again.

132
00:07:19,771 --> 00:07:21,441
You really love bringing up the law.

133
00:07:24,371 --> 00:07:25,512
Wait for me.

134
00:07:26,171 --> 00:07:27,271
What?

135
00:07:27,271 --> 00:07:28,304
Wait for me.

136
00:07:29,015 --> 00:07:30,617
(ALPHA AI Global Algorithm Fund)

137
00:07:31,757 --> 00:07:35,222
They said it would rise starting today,
and it really did.

138
00:07:36,204 --> 00:07:37,590
Ten percent in just one day?

139
00:07:40,104 --> 00:07:42,228
I only managed to invest 2,000 dollars.

140
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:50,070
(Global Corporate Investment
Algorithm Project Tester Recruitment)

141
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:53,006
(Open the link?)

142
00:07:55,798 --> 00:07:57,944
A minimum return of 40 percent?

143
00:08:01,271 --> 00:08:04,004
Honey, I'm home.

144
00:08:04,004 --> 00:08:06,052
Hey, you're late.

145
00:08:06,704 --> 00:08:08,321
What about dinner?

146
00:08:08,671 --> 00:08:10,304
I just ordered something simple
with the director.

147
00:08:10,304 --> 00:08:11,358
What about Bit Na?

148
00:08:12,204 --> 00:08:15,562
She said she'd wait for you
but fell asleep just now.

149
00:08:16,471 --> 00:08:18,298
Teaching at the academy is fun,

150
00:08:18,830 --> 00:08:21,430
but I feel bad
that I get less time with Bit Na.

151
00:08:22,104 --> 00:08:24,104
Other dads are all the same.

152
00:08:25,453 --> 00:08:27,871
By the way, do you happen to have...

153
00:08:27,871 --> 00:08:29,609
any cash on you?

154
00:08:29,990 --> 00:08:31,745
Cash? Yeah.

155
00:08:33,977 --> 00:08:36,944
This is all I have.
I always keep some for emergencies.

156
00:08:37,271 --> 00:08:38,371
Why? Do you want it?

157
00:08:38,371 --> 00:08:40,371
No, it's fine.

158
00:08:41,817 --> 00:08:44,057
My first paycheck is coming soon,
so just wait a little.

159
00:08:44,871 --> 00:08:47,027
The director said
if I get more than 30 students,

160
00:08:47,027 --> 00:08:48,962
I'll start getting incentives too.

161
00:08:49,771 --> 00:08:51,064
I'll go check on Bit Na.

162
00:08:51,064 --> 00:08:52,064
Okay.

163
00:09:00,077 --> 00:09:01,977
Is there any way
I could get a lump sum of money?

164
00:09:06,611 --> 00:09:08,682
You don't have to prepare my meals.

165
00:09:10,237 --> 00:09:11,310
How could I not?

166
00:09:11,310 --> 00:09:13,920
You're not a stranger.
You're my daughter's boss.

167
00:09:14,671 --> 00:09:17,971
Starting tomorrow,
I'll leave early before everyone wakes up.

168
00:09:17,971 --> 00:09:19,125
You don't need to worry about me.

169
00:09:19,297 --> 00:09:20,737
No need to feel any pressure.

170
00:09:20,904 --> 00:09:23,963
It's just one extra bowl of rice
with what we already eat.

171
00:09:24,224 --> 00:09:27,424
Mom, Dad, Team Manager says
he'll be moving out soon.

172
00:09:27,936 --> 00:09:29,736
Mom, put the room back on the market.

173
00:09:29,736 --> 00:09:31,704
No, I have absolutely no intention
of moving out.

174
00:09:32,204 --> 00:09:33,740
The Housing Lease Protection Act.

175
00:09:34,004 --> 00:09:35,241
What law?

176
00:09:35,924 --> 00:09:37,811
- Here we go again.
- Hey.

177
00:09:39,030 --> 00:09:42,520
Instead of that, how about...

178
00:09:42,704 --> 00:09:45,552
you just have two meals a day with us,
like a boarding arrangement?

179
00:09:45,552 --> 00:09:47,370
What? Boarding?

180
00:09:47,371 --> 00:09:51,004
We're living in the same house.
It feels bad to leave you out for meals.

181
00:09:51,277 --> 00:09:53,526
You might feel pressured
if I say it's free,

182
00:09:54,184 --> 00:09:55,795
so I'll charge you for meals separately.

183
00:09:55,795 --> 00:09:57,030
Mom!

184
00:09:58,118 --> 00:09:59,604
Is that really okay?

185
00:09:59,604 --> 00:10:00,800
Team Manager!

186
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:03,903
What's wrong? It's a win-win.

187
00:10:04,104 --> 00:10:06,337
Mom can earn meal fees on top of rent.
Perfect.

188
00:10:06,337 --> 00:10:08,537
And you get both room and board sorted.
Perfect.

189
00:10:08,904 --> 00:10:10,443
Stop saying "perfect."

190
00:10:11,071 --> 00:10:12,671
I think that sounds good too.

191
00:10:12,671 --> 00:10:14,471
It's not long anyway, just four months.

192
00:10:14,964 --> 00:10:16,171
Let's do that.

193
00:10:16,171 --> 00:10:17,817
I'd be grateful if you would.

194
00:10:17,817 --> 00:10:20,320
But why is the contract for four months?

195
00:10:21,204 --> 00:10:22,824
Once I finish this project,

196
00:10:22,824 --> 00:10:24,357
I have to return to the U.S.

197
00:10:26,511 --> 00:10:27,994
Did you live in the U.S. before?

198
00:10:28,671 --> 00:10:31,471
Why? Will you ask him for English lessons?

199
00:10:31,717 --> 00:10:33,032
What are you talking about?

200
00:10:33,704 --> 00:10:36,236
Yes, I came here for a bit
due to personal reasons.

201
00:10:41,591 --> 00:10:42,871
Hurry up, Team Manager.

202
00:10:42,871 --> 00:10:43,871
- Yes.
- Stop.

203
00:10:44,371 --> 00:10:46,980
Hold it right there.
What is this situation?

204
00:10:47,204 --> 00:10:48,515
Why are you coming out of there?

205
00:10:49,071 --> 00:10:50,817
I live at Ms. Cho Eun Ae's house.

206
00:10:51,017 --> 00:10:52,017
What?

207
00:10:52,371 --> 00:10:53,987
Why would you put it like that?

208
00:10:54,204 --> 00:10:55,671
Cho Rong, it's not like that.

209
00:10:55,671 --> 00:10:57,523
My mom said she was renting out a room,
remember?

210
00:10:57,523 --> 00:10:59,159
He's the tenant.

211
00:10:59,904 --> 00:11:03,396
The tenant.
So he's staying in your old room?

212
00:11:03,571 --> 00:11:04,631
Yeah, that's right.

213
00:11:04,984 --> 00:11:06,399
We're in a hurry to get to work. Bye.

214
00:11:07,271 --> 00:11:08,271
That won't do.

215
00:11:08,471 --> 00:11:09,971
Since when? And what's your intention?

216
00:11:09,971 --> 00:11:11,071
Who suggested it first?

217
00:11:11,071 --> 00:11:12,472
So how does it feel,
living in Eun Ae's room?

218
00:11:13,371 --> 00:11:14,930
That's a lot of questions.

219
00:11:14,930 --> 00:11:16,797
May I give you a detailed briefing later?

220
00:11:17,977 --> 00:11:20,747
Sure. Have a nice day.

221
00:11:21,371 --> 00:11:24,271
Thanks for letting us go so easily,
my friend.

222
00:11:24,271 --> 00:11:26,486
- Let's go.
- Bye then.

223
00:11:28,523 --> 00:11:29,889
What's going on?

224
00:11:30,071 --> 00:11:32,759
What is this unexpected development?

225
00:11:33,704 --> 00:11:34,943
Even my heart's fluttering.

226
00:11:43,304 --> 00:11:44,571
Does it really have to be like this?

227
00:11:44,771 --> 00:11:46,871
Is this the best option? Are you sure?

228
00:11:47,071 --> 00:11:48,671
Then what do you want me to do?

229
00:11:48,671 --> 00:11:51,361
If you don't like it,
find another way to get around.

230
00:11:54,884 --> 00:11:56,149
You used my shampoo again, didn't you?

231
00:11:57,721 --> 00:11:59,771
If anyone asks, just say...

232
00:11:59,771 --> 00:12:02,471
it's a popular shampoo
from a home shopping deal.

233
00:12:02,471 --> 00:12:05,425
And try to order your own shampoo
as soon as possible.

234
00:12:06,524 --> 00:12:08,504
You're really stingy over shampoo.

235
00:12:08,504 --> 00:12:10,863
It's not that.
People keep saying we smell the same.

236
00:12:10,863 --> 00:12:12,465
I'll buy you ten bottles of shampoo.

237
00:12:12,498 --> 00:12:13,900
That's not a bad offer.

238
00:12:14,671 --> 00:12:17,770
Anyway, don't forget to wait ten minutes
before you go up.

239
00:12:17,971 --> 00:12:19,105
Understood.

240
00:12:20,304 --> 00:12:21,304
I'm off.

241
00:12:38,571 --> 00:12:40,071
I'm going to the Chief's office.

242
00:12:40,071 --> 00:12:41,471
We'll have a meeting in 30 minutes.

243
00:12:41,731 --> 00:12:43,131
- Yes, understood.
- Understood.

244
00:12:48,204 --> 00:12:50,103
Come to the meeting room for a sec.

245
00:12:57,071 --> 00:12:58,144
What the?

246
00:13:03,604 --> 00:13:04,604
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

247
00:13:05,477 --> 00:13:06,586
No, Eun Ae.

248
00:13:07,384 --> 00:13:09,288
The more I think about it,
the more this doesn't seem right.

249
00:13:10,011 --> 00:13:12,859
What are you talking about? Speak clearly.

250
00:13:12,859 --> 00:13:15,828
I saw you and the Team Manager
coming to work together.

251
00:13:16,996 --> 00:13:19,432
I know you're pretending to like him...

252
00:13:19,432 --> 00:13:20,900
to make me jealous.

253
00:13:21,504 --> 00:13:23,936
But even so, using him like that...

254
00:13:24,171 --> 00:13:26,139
isn't right.

255
00:13:26,404 --> 00:13:28,107
What are you even saying?

256
00:13:28,671 --> 00:13:30,004
Hey, Mr. Han Ji Hun,

257
00:13:30,004 --> 00:13:33,171
you've been out of my life
for a long time already.

258
00:13:33,171 --> 00:13:34,647
Out of my mind.

259
00:13:35,171 --> 00:13:38,251
What? I'm out?

260
00:13:38,251 --> 00:13:40,520
Yeah, out. Eliminated this season.

261
00:13:40,520 --> 00:13:43,156
Demoted to the minors. Retired. Period.

262
00:13:44,404 --> 00:13:46,404
How can you be like this?

263
00:13:46,404 --> 00:13:47,927
How can love change?

264
00:13:54,871 --> 00:13:55,871
You said it yourself before, didn't you?

265
00:13:56,471 --> 00:14:00,004
You said that my temper
is why I'm not popular with guys.

266
00:14:01,071 --> 00:14:04,271
Don't poke a sleeping bunny's whiskers.

267
00:14:11,171 --> 00:14:12,371
No...

268
00:14:12,971 --> 00:14:15,121
The Cho Eun Ae I know would never change.

269
00:14:16,871 --> 00:14:20,860
Love comes back around!

270
00:14:22,671 --> 00:14:24,997
Did you have a good time
with Gyeol yesterday?

271
00:14:26,238 --> 00:14:28,301
No comment on personal questions.

272
00:14:28,571 --> 00:14:30,069
Okay, got it.

273
00:14:31,837 --> 00:14:34,474
Then shall we get back
to official business?

274
00:14:35,171 --> 00:14:36,971
The meeting is set
for 30 minutes from now.

275
00:14:36,971 --> 00:14:39,612
Cancel it.
We have to go out on business now.

276
00:14:41,283 --> 00:14:44,617
Chief, please go with another employee
from now on.

277
00:14:44,617 --> 00:14:47,820
What's with you? I give the orders.

278
00:14:47,971 --> 00:14:49,822
You follow my instructions, Manager Seo.

279
00:14:53,251 --> 00:14:54,761
It just doesn't sit right with me.

280
00:14:55,304 --> 00:14:56,583
I mean, if he glanced at the documents...

281
00:14:56,583 --> 00:14:59,183
and figured out the cash flow, it could...

282
00:15:00,504 --> 00:15:01,604
I don't even want to think about it.

283
00:15:02,171 --> 00:15:03,171
Isn't there anything...

284
00:15:03,471 --> 00:15:06,239
that could draw Seong Jun's attention
elsewhere?

285
00:15:08,404 --> 00:15:09,471
Genius.

286
00:15:11,204 --> 00:15:13,513
Mr. Cho, come in for a moment.

287
00:15:22,437 --> 00:15:23,437
You called for me?

288
00:15:26,671 --> 00:15:30,200
Sit down. My neck hurts looking up at you.
So sit.

289
00:15:33,971 --> 00:15:38,004
Judging by the recent competition results,

290
00:15:38,691 --> 00:15:41,991
it seems like Team One's project
will be finalized.

291
00:15:42,171 --> 00:15:44,604
Mr. Cho, you look into a site.

292
00:15:45,371 --> 00:15:46,671
What? A site?

293
00:15:46,671 --> 00:15:48,490
Well, it's not finalized yet,

294
00:15:48,490 --> 00:15:51,490
but go ahead and do a preliminary survey.

295
00:15:51,950 --> 00:15:54,017
Also, check the budget...

296
00:15:54,304 --> 00:15:56,088
and whether the project is viable, okay?

297
00:15:57,204 --> 00:15:59,544
There are still two rounds left.

298
00:15:59,544 --> 00:16:01,704
I think it's too early for that.

299
00:16:01,704 --> 00:16:03,171
Too early... Mr. Cho,

300
00:16:03,904 --> 00:16:06,232
I've been in construction for 35 years.

301
00:16:06,671 --> 00:16:09,104
I've developed an instinct.

302
00:16:09,104 --> 00:16:11,671
I can tell at a glance
who'll make it and who won't.

303
00:16:13,331 --> 00:16:16,391
This may be an impertinent question,

304
00:16:16,391 --> 00:16:18,791
but why do you treat
your two sons so differently?

305
00:16:19,011 --> 00:16:20,631
Differently? What, are you saying...

306
00:16:20,631 --> 00:16:23,750
I favor my eldest son, Min Ho?

307
00:16:23,971 --> 00:16:25,885
Yes, that's how it seems.

308
00:16:26,023 --> 00:16:27,304
Don't twist my words.

309
00:16:27,304 --> 00:16:30,323
I'm doing this
for the future of Kangsu Construction.

310
00:16:31,358 --> 00:16:32,358
Let's see.

311
00:16:33,059 --> 00:16:35,027
If we go with Team Two's design...

312
00:16:35,304 --> 00:16:36,604
No, it won't even get that far.

313
00:16:36,604 --> 00:16:39,665
But if we do, we won't see profits at all.

314
00:16:39,665 --> 00:16:41,334
That's not necessarily true.

315
00:16:42,174 --> 00:16:45,345
Team One's retirement community,
from its central location...

316
00:16:45,345 --> 00:16:47,671
to its luxury construction,

317
00:16:47,671 --> 00:16:49,671
will require massive funding
from the start.

318
00:16:50,171 --> 00:16:51,911
There's also a risk...

319
00:16:51,911 --> 00:16:55,681
that it won't be profitable.
For example...

320
00:16:56,704 --> 00:16:58,017
Mr. Cho, that's enough.

321
00:16:58,671 --> 00:17:01,420
Did you work like that at Samho too?

322
00:17:01,737 --> 00:17:04,390
Talking back to your superiors like that?

323
00:17:04,624 --> 00:17:07,360
No wonder
you were subject to restructuring.

324
00:17:09,629 --> 00:17:10,696
I'll correct that.

325
00:17:12,033 --> 00:17:14,100
Go and look into that site right away.

326
00:17:15,004 --> 00:17:16,871
Yes, understood.

327
00:17:19,610 --> 00:17:20,873
Go, now.

328
00:17:22,871 --> 00:17:24,771
Acting all cool...

329
00:17:27,871 --> 00:17:29,115
This won't be easy.

330
00:17:30,150 --> 00:17:33,853
How did Father end up
with an assistant like Gwon Sik?

331
00:17:36,397 --> 00:17:38,557
I think Yong Man was much better.

332
00:17:45,604 --> 00:17:46,604
Hey, Ms. Cho.

333
00:17:49,431 --> 00:17:52,379
Working out is essential during work.

334
00:17:52,379 --> 00:17:55,808
I use my arms and shoulders a lot.

335
00:17:58,671 --> 00:17:59,671
Excuse me.

336
00:18:00,171 --> 00:18:01,171
Yes?

337
00:18:04,191 --> 00:18:07,687
It's not "excuse me," it's Seo Seung Wu.

338
00:18:10,871 --> 00:18:12,971
I have something to say, so come sit down.

339
00:18:16,804 --> 00:18:17,804
Okay.

340
00:18:23,404 --> 00:18:26,463
I'm not usually this picky,

341
00:18:26,463 --> 00:18:28,274
but I get sensitive when I'm working,

342
00:18:29,006 --> 00:18:30,671
like if someone keeps fidgeting beside me,

343
00:18:30,671 --> 00:18:32,371
talks loudly on the phone,

344
00:18:32,371 --> 00:18:35,281
or brings in outsiders, things like that.

345
00:18:35,281 --> 00:18:38,271
My goodness, I'm exactly the same.

346
00:18:38,271 --> 00:18:39,730
What I absolutely can't stand...

347
00:18:39,730 --> 00:18:41,820
are noise, messiness, and...

348
00:18:43,491 --> 00:18:44,824
fashion terrorists.

349
00:18:45,571 --> 00:18:47,593
What?

350
00:18:48,571 --> 00:18:50,997
What is this?
The perverted psycho and me...

351
00:18:51,530 --> 00:18:53,165
in the same room?

352
00:18:54,171 --> 00:18:55,801
I wasn't talking about you.

353
00:18:56,704 --> 00:19:00,904
Anyway, how about we set usage hours?

354
00:19:00,904 --> 00:19:03,971
What? Hours? How?

355
00:19:03,971 --> 00:19:06,771
Nine to nine.
I'll use it from 9 a.m. to 9 p.m.,

356
00:19:06,771 --> 00:19:08,971
you use it from 9 p.m. to 9 a.m.

357
00:19:08,971 --> 00:19:12,370
What? Then I'll basically be a night owl.

358
00:19:12,844 --> 00:19:16,704
Or I take 7 a.m. to 7 p.m.,

359
00:19:16,704 --> 00:19:18,004
and you take 7 p.m...

360
00:19:18,004 --> 00:19:20,671
So basically,
you'll use it during the day...

361
00:19:20,671 --> 00:19:24,230
and I'll use it at night?

362
00:19:26,944 --> 00:19:29,940
Well, I am more of a night owl.

363
00:19:30,217 --> 00:19:31,517
Sure, fine.

364
00:19:32,571 --> 00:19:33,639
Then...

365
00:19:34,804 --> 00:19:36,942
It's 2 p.m. now, so...

366
00:19:37,404 --> 00:19:38,404
Wait.

367
00:19:39,104 --> 00:19:42,181
Are you telling me to leave right now?

368
00:19:42,710 --> 00:19:45,510
Not today. Starting next week.

369
00:19:47,671 --> 00:19:49,271
Seriously...

370
00:19:55,671 --> 00:19:59,651
Hey, Hye Ji. It's been so long.

371
00:20:00,271 --> 00:20:01,271
Are you okay?

372
00:20:01,797 --> 00:20:04,264
Last time,
your mom was in front of the ER...

373
00:20:04,704 --> 00:20:05,937
About telling my mom I dropped out?

374
00:20:06,271 --> 00:20:08,271
It's fine. It turned out for the better.

375
00:20:09,204 --> 00:20:11,931
You want to meet? Okay, sure.

376
00:20:12,390 --> 00:20:13,390
Wait.

377
00:20:14,871 --> 00:20:17,505
I have a studio.
I'll send you the address,

378
00:20:17,505 --> 00:20:20,042
so come anytime. Okay, bye.

379
00:20:21,724 --> 00:20:22,724
Ms. Cho.

380
00:20:23,404 --> 00:20:25,671
You just said no outsiders allowed.

381
00:20:25,671 --> 00:20:27,104
Didn't I hear that wrong?

382
00:20:27,104 --> 00:20:28,160
What?

383
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:31,330
Are you a goldfish?
Did you already forget what you just said?

384
00:20:31,330 --> 00:20:32,765
What? A goldfish?

385
00:20:32,771 --> 00:20:34,066
Yeah, a goldfish!

386
00:20:35,267 --> 00:20:37,371
You! How old are you?

387
00:20:37,371 --> 00:20:39,004
Show me your ID.

388
00:20:39,271 --> 00:20:41,871
Sure! What, you think I won't?

389
00:20:41,871 --> 00:20:43,127
Hey, come here. Seriously.

390
00:20:43,127 --> 00:20:44,154
Come here.

391
00:20:44,154 --> 00:20:45,544
- What?
- I'm here, so what?

392
00:20:45,544 --> 00:20:46,846
Show me your ID.

393
00:20:46,846 --> 00:20:48,671
- How old are you?
- Seriously.

394
00:20:58,271 --> 00:21:01,924
Are you planning to install an arcade
in our retirement community?

395
00:21:02,571 --> 00:21:03,863
Of course not.

396
00:21:04,197 --> 00:21:06,799
I'm going to try all the games here...

397
00:21:06,799 --> 00:21:08,904
and choose sports...

398
00:21:09,071 --> 00:21:10,604
that can be applied to our project.

399
00:21:11,804 --> 00:21:14,173
All right, what should we try first?

400
00:21:22,877 --> 00:21:24,510
Okay, shooting.

401
00:21:25,750 --> 00:21:28,104
You know I served in the Marines, right?

402
00:21:28,104 --> 00:21:29,671
When I was training,

403
00:21:29,671 --> 00:21:32,338
I even got a reward leave for my shooting.

404
00:21:35,804 --> 00:21:39,632
Chief, I don't need your sympathy.

405
00:21:41,671 --> 00:21:43,135
What? Sympathy?

406
00:21:44,071 --> 00:21:47,244
It seems like you're assuming I was hurt
by the team manager last night...

407
00:21:47,244 --> 00:21:50,477
and trying to comfort me.

408
00:21:51,451 --> 00:21:53,484
I don't need this kind of comfort.

409
00:21:54,915 --> 00:21:55,915
Then...

410
00:21:56,804 --> 00:21:57,871
Stop right there, Manager Seo.

411
00:22:00,871 --> 00:22:03,104
Wasn't it your principle...

412
00:22:03,104 --> 00:22:04,404
not to mix personal feelings with work?

413
00:22:05,971 --> 00:22:08,794
Why can't you separate the two these days?

414
00:22:11,171 --> 00:22:13,032
Try all the games here,

415
00:22:13,290 --> 00:22:16,023
and submit a detailed report
by tomorrow...

416
00:22:16,671 --> 00:22:19,571
on which ones
we should include in our project.

417
00:23:12,404 --> 00:23:15,494
Are you sure
you don't want me to come with you?

418
00:23:15,494 --> 00:23:17,896
It's just a routine checkup.

419
00:23:18,471 --> 00:23:19,832
Mr. Seo will be with me.

420
00:23:20,404 --> 00:23:22,371
Yes, Madam. Don't worry.

421
00:23:22,371 --> 00:23:24,071
I'll take good care of him.

422
00:23:24,071 --> 00:23:27,250
- All right, do your thing. I'll be back.
- Yes.

423
00:23:27,250 --> 00:23:28,250
We'll be back.

424
00:23:31,930 --> 00:23:34,480
When will you go grocery shopping?

425
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:36,671
I'll have the car ready.

426
00:23:37,304 --> 00:23:40,953
Let's go now. I'll get ready quickly.

427
00:23:45,043 --> 00:23:46,943
At her age, going to the market herself...

428
00:23:48,671 --> 00:23:49,995
Seriously.

429
00:23:50,271 --> 00:23:52,110
I'm busy too.

430
00:23:52,271 --> 00:23:54,433
I need to order desserts and champagne.

431
00:23:56,424 --> 00:23:57,424
Hello?

432
00:23:58,238 --> 00:23:59,905
Is this the Freesia Hotel bakery team?

433
00:24:00,471 --> 00:24:03,015
Yes, I'd like to place a dessert order.

434
00:24:11,004 --> 00:24:12,618
We're heading out. What about lunch?

435
00:24:13,582 --> 00:24:14,650
We are not kids.

436
00:24:14,650 --> 00:24:16,750
We'll take care of lunch ourselves.
Don't worry.

437
00:24:16,971 --> 00:24:20,826
She's not worried about us.
She's worried about the Team Manager.

438
00:24:21,527 --> 00:24:24,196
I plan to go to the office,
so don't worry.

439
00:24:24,311 --> 00:24:25,631
The office? All of a sudden?

440
00:24:26,271 --> 00:24:28,767
You won't mention I'm staying here, right?

441
00:24:29,818 --> 00:24:30,918
You worry too much.

442
00:24:31,204 --> 00:24:32,804
- Let's go.
- We'll be back.

443
00:24:32,804 --> 00:24:33,804
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

444
00:24:33,804 --> 00:24:34,804
See you.

445
00:24:39,684 --> 00:24:41,384
I'll head to the studio soon too.

446
00:24:41,648 --> 00:24:43,048
So it'll just be the two of you at home.

447
00:24:43,371 --> 00:24:45,050
So what? What are you trying to say?

448
00:24:45,571 --> 00:24:48,066
I'm going to go to the office too,
so if it's because of me, you can stay.

449
00:24:48,066 --> 00:24:51,619
No, I'm a writer with a studio, you know?

450
00:24:51,911 --> 00:24:53,859
What's with your tone all of a sudden?

451
00:24:53,859 --> 00:24:56,791
Eun Ae, usually on your days off,

452
00:24:56,791 --> 00:24:59,832
you don't even wash your face
and just wear sweats.

453
00:25:00,603 --> 00:25:03,136
But now, makeup and a flowy dress...

454
00:25:03,771 --> 00:25:05,938
This is so unfamiliar.

455
00:25:05,938 --> 00:25:07,406
Hey, when was I like that?

456
00:25:09,964 --> 00:25:13,257
I've seen everything
from sleep marks, drool,

457
00:25:13,257 --> 00:25:15,714
and all your drunken antics.

458
00:25:16,471 --> 00:25:18,071
This is unfamiliar to me too.

459
00:25:18,071 --> 00:25:19,071
What did you say?

460
00:25:20,371 --> 00:25:21,754
What are you doing today?

461
00:25:21,754 --> 00:25:22,804
None of your business.

462
00:25:26,771 --> 00:25:29,889
Once Seong Jun joins,

463
00:25:30,544 --> 00:25:32,764
the three of you
will have a lot to talk about.

464
00:25:33,917 --> 00:25:36,468
Yes. He should be here soon.

465
00:25:39,004 --> 00:25:41,073
Honey, come here for a second.

466
00:25:41,604 --> 00:25:43,175
What is it?

467
00:25:45,904 --> 00:25:47,613
How do I look? Natural?

468
00:25:50,104 --> 00:25:52,684
Well, not exactly natural...

469
00:25:53,097 --> 00:25:54,097
Yeah, natural.

470
00:25:54,570 --> 00:25:56,770
It's obvious you tried hard
not to make it obvious,

471
00:25:56,771 --> 00:25:58,757
which makes it awkward in a good way.

472
00:25:58,957 --> 00:26:00,192
What are you saying?

473
00:26:02,371 --> 00:26:04,096
What is that, a palm tree?

474
00:26:04,904 --> 00:26:07,633
I told you to stay away from the kitchen
since you're a guest today.

475
00:26:07,871 --> 00:26:09,835
How am I a guest?

476
00:26:10,104 --> 00:26:13,772
With you working this hard,
of course I should help.

477
00:26:14,171 --> 00:26:15,474
Is everything ready?

478
00:26:18,571 --> 00:26:21,804
Mother, will beef hot pot
and fermented oysters...

479
00:26:21,804 --> 00:26:24,016
go well with French desserts?

480
00:26:24,756 --> 00:26:27,886
Then come and cook something that matches.

481
00:26:27,886 --> 00:26:29,471
No.

482
00:26:29,471 --> 00:26:32,604
Actually,
the East-West combination is very good.

483
00:26:32,604 --> 00:26:33,759
Très bien.

484
00:26:36,811 --> 00:26:37,911
They must be here.

485
00:26:37,911 --> 00:26:39,565
That top-of-the-class janitor friend
and his wife.

486
00:26:40,871 --> 00:26:42,000
My goodness.

487
00:26:42,671 --> 00:26:44,770
Why is she so excited?

488
00:26:48,964 --> 00:26:51,271
Chairman, hello.

489
00:26:51,271 --> 00:26:53,445
Come on in.

490
00:26:53,445 --> 00:26:54,947
I've been waiting.

491
00:26:56,404 --> 00:26:57,471
This is my wife.

492
00:26:58,404 --> 00:26:59,952
Nice to meet you, Chairman.

493
00:27:00,171 --> 00:27:02,387
Yes, welcome.

494
00:27:02,387 --> 00:27:04,571
I'm Seong Jun's friend...

495
00:27:04,571 --> 00:27:07,392
and the CEO of Kangsu Construction,
Ko Dae Chi. Nice to meet you.

496
00:27:08,471 --> 00:27:10,195
Nice to meet you.

497
00:27:11,331 --> 00:27:13,299
Bienvenue! Welcome!

498
00:27:14,704 --> 00:27:15,704
Hello...

499
00:27:19,237 --> 00:27:20,572
Honey, help me with this.

500
00:27:22,276 --> 00:27:24,271
My goodness. Ms. Kang Yeon Ja.

501
00:27:26,804 --> 00:27:29,248
What's going on? Why is everyone...

502
00:27:30,471 --> 00:27:32,771
Then Min Ho's mom is...

503
00:27:32,771 --> 00:27:34,253
Yes, that's right.

504
00:27:34,571 --> 00:27:37,356
I'm CEO Ko Dae Chi's wife.

505
00:27:37,671 --> 00:27:39,691
What is going on?

506
00:27:39,971 --> 00:27:42,794
The real estate lady
from our line dancing class...

507
00:27:45,904 --> 00:27:49,566
The three of us take the same class
at the community center.

508
00:27:50,471 --> 00:27:53,372
Come on in, everyone. Let's eat.

509
00:27:53,372 --> 00:27:55,239
Hey, Seong Jun, remember my mother?

510
00:27:56,271 --> 00:27:58,110
Hello, I'm Cho Seong Jun.

511
00:27:58,110 --> 00:28:00,177
Yes, welcome.

512
00:28:00,624 --> 00:28:01,624
Ma'am.

513
00:28:04,671 --> 00:28:06,271
What?

514
00:28:23,302 --> 00:28:25,037
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
